112. F. lagopus (Rough-legged Falcon).

We are informed by Mr. Scales of Beechamwell, near Swafl'- ham, that this bird annually visits the warren at that place about the month of November, and continues there for some time in quest of rabbits. A fine bird of this species, which ΜΓ. S. kept alive many months, is now preserved in the British Museuin. Not long since, a pair of Rough-legged Falcons were killed at Holkhani ; and we have heard of one which was shot at Butley in suffolk.
